emand plan and inventory inputs to determine net supply needs; Create the long term supply plan with some oversight from manager for assigned products or locations; With some oversight, review network capacity capabilities and trends with Master Production Planners; Provide potential solutions for the business to review when available capacity does not meet requirements; Reviews capacity on a daily basis for assigned products or locations and develops plans to service customers through any shortages; Collaborates with all relevant stakeholders in the process using a substantial understanding of supply chain planning practices and procedures; Under supervision, generate and execute cycle stock and safety stock plans for the assigned products or locations, utilizing the approved supply plan inputs; With some oversight, create the finished goods inventory plans for assigned product(s) or locations, and provide for business review; Recevie and create orders for network distribution moves and communicate to logistics for execution; With minimal guidance, manage inventory levels to expected volume and working capital levels and provide solutions when business parameters change requiring a change to inventory expectations; Provides input in setting Supply and Inventory Planning metrics targets; Analyze actual measure vs. target measures for assigned product(s) or locations; Provide input and insight in developing action plans to close gaps between target and actual measures; Provides continual Supply and Inventory Planning process improvement input; Provides assistance in root cause analysis to identify and correct supply and inventory deviations; 30% Other Collect all documents for onboarding counterparties (suppliers, customers, internal Cargill entities); Collecting documentation required for the payment of foreign currencies; Provide support in setting and following up counterparty risk limits (credit and storage); Reporting : Produce and action execution of daily report of actual exposures versus approved limits; Invoicing/payments: Prepare documents to be sent to CBS for payment of all accounting orders; Assist in managing all contracts (in MBS) related matters and orders closing; Assist the Account Manager to track customer\u2019s overdue and other related paybles/receivebles; Prepare inventory valuation (in MBS) and pass this to finance to validate; Liase with business manager and Plant Operation on business matters and work with finance team so everthing is understood and correct in P&L; Follow CBI and conciliate with internal CASC SC protocols to guarantee full compliance with Cargill and Local (RSA) policies. Qualifications Qualifications Bachelor's degree in Business Admin or Related Field 3+ years of professional experience in supply planning Flexible, able to work independently, set and follow priorities, manage multiple tasks and deadlines effectively. International outlook/experience, full professional proficiency in English (both verbal and written), additional languages an advantage. Good with PowerPoint, Excel and data analytics tools Solution oriented and pro-active in case of possible deviation from the agreed upon goals Dedicated and diligent Ability to work as part of a team Adaptable to change Interested? Then make sure to send us your CV and cover letter in English today. Follow us on LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/cargill Job Supply Chain Management Primary Location South Africa-GT-Johannesburg Schedule Full-time Job Type Standard Shift Day Job Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Privacy | TermsÂ |Â Privacy Center"
